rComments: Made my freshman year what it was. I would do anything to be back in his classes, they were memorable and excitable. He is understanding, helpful, and animates his lessons. You will learn well.
Funny guy, Italian 100%, helpful, he knows about life and academic life, not only about what he has to teach his students - a spoonful of humour in each class

Sebastiano is really helpful, he makes his lectures fun. But beware of his jokes as he can get mouthful-- he swears quite a bit but it's all for good humor. If you have an easy going personality, chances are you'll get along with him -- meaning better grades.
